Why does everyone make it sound like having the most lines/screen time is a gift? There is so much responsibility and criticism that comes with it. You guys have any idea how hard it must be for Mia to handle all the lines and spotlight her company has put her under?

Sure, I agree it’d be better if everyone got equal lines but this sort of thing isn’t uncommon. Especially for a group as new as them. Once they get established, the fairness will begin to show. Mia undoubtably has the strongest dancing skills and most stable voice, so it’s not a suprise why she has the most attention.

Also, Yuehua know what they’re doing. The producers know what they are doing. If you want a song to sound like shit, then I suggest all the “professionals” in the comment section and the ones targeting Mia should go rent a couple hours in a studio session and make a track of their own.
